## Where the gaps and open decisions live
Everything the source docs **do not** settle — cross-document conflicts, modules without screens,
logic named but not defined, and decisions only the owner can make — is captured in
**[REQUIREMENTS-DIGEST-AND-GAPS.md](REQUIREMENTS-DIGEST-AND-GAPS.md)** (produced with `GAP-ANALYSIS.template`).
Open questions from it are promoted into `../DECISIONS.md` as each module comes up. Read the digest
before starting any slice.

## The three inputs (why nothing falls through)
- **Requirements (this KB)** = WHAT to build.
- **Standards (`../standards-kb/`)** = HOW WELL — obeyed for all NFRs.
- **Design tokens (`../design-system-kb/`)** = HOW IT LOOKS — obeyed for all UI.
